description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2r09e","text":"This protocol describes an approach that can be used to quantifiy the rate dependence of cardiac action potential duration.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
keywords: cardiac action potential, restitution, action potential duration rate dependence

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"52u2m","text":"Membrane potentials were recorded from isolated pig ventricular myocytes using the whole-cell configuration of the patch clamp technique.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5naln","text":"Isolated cells were placed in a perfusion chamber on the stage of an inverted microscope and bathed in an extracellular solution containing (in mM) NaCl 140, KCl 5.4, CaCl22.5, MgCl2 0.5, glucose 5.5, and HEPES 5 (pH 7.4), maintained at 37°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4cvbk","text":"Cells were patched using microelectrodes with resistances between 1 and 2 MΩ.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7jfej","text":"Cells were dialyzed with an intracellular solution containing (in mM): K-aspartate 110, KCl 25, NaCl 5, MgATP 3, cAMP 0.002, phosphocreatine dipotassium 10, EGTA 0.01, and HEPES 10 (pH 7.2).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"akfue","text":"Membrane potential was recorded under current clamp conditions using a Multiclamp 700B voltage clamp amplifier, Digidata 1440A computer interface, and pClamp 11 data acquisition and analysis software (Molecular Devices). Data were lowpass filtered at 4 kHz, and sampled at 10 kHz.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"507ch","text":"Action potentials (APs) were elicited by applying a depolarizing stimulus approximately 2 ms in duration. The amplitude of the stimulus was adjusted to approximately 1.2x the minimum value needed to trigger an AP.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f67k1","text":"Cells were not used if the resting membrane potential was less than -75 mV, the stimulus artifact overlapped the upstroke of the AP, or a stable baseline could not be established.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5t4oo","text":"AP restitution was evaluated by triggering an AP once every 800 ms for 20 beats to establish a baseline. The stimulus interval was then reduced by 20 ms each subsequent beat for 10 beats, then by 10 ms each beat for 20 beats, and then by 5 ms each beat until we observed AP duration alternans or it was no longer possible to elicit an AP.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6nnku","text":"Myocytes were then exposed to test drug. During this period a new baseline was established by recording APs elicited once every 5 s for approximately 5 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c23r3","text":"Drug effects were then evaluated by repeating the restitution protocol outlined in step 8.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5hre2","text":"Data were analyzed by measuring the duration of each AP recorded during the restitution protocol and plotting it as a function of the preceding diastolic interval (time between 90% repolarization of the previous AP and upstroke of the current AP).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"chmpj","text":"The slope of the restitution curve was then measured as the first derivative of the polynomial fit to the data at the shortest diastolic interval.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Cardiac Action Potential Restitution Protocol
